wndwalk - improved virtual desktop navigation on MS Windows
===========================================================

Tutorial
--------

    [Alt]+[{1..9}]          - switch to another desktop
    [Alt]+[p]               - launch wndmenu (optional)
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[{1..9}]  - send focused window to another desktop
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[Enter]   - launch terminal
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[q]       - log out
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[c]       - close focused window
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[f]       - float focused window
    [Alt]+[Shift]+[m]       - maximize focused window


Building from Source
====================

This project supports building from source on Windows using CMake and Visual
Studio Build Tools.

Requirements
------------

Visual Studio Build Tools 2022: https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/

Configuration
-------------

Configuration is done by modifying src/config.hpp as desired and (re)compiling.

Build instructions
------------------

* Open x64 Native Tools Command Prompt for VS 2022
* Build the project:

    mkdir build
    cd build
    cmake .. -G "NMake Makefiles"
    nmake

* The resulting executable (wndwalk.exe) will be located in the build directory.


Troubleshooting
===============

* Make sure you are using the x64 Native Tools Command Prompt â€” not the x86 or
  generic command prompt.
